value.value: The sole is the bottom of the foot.
The gastric glands in the pyloric region of the stomach; the pyloric glands secrete mucin, which coats the stomach and protects it, and hormones such as gastrin and enkephalin[MP].
A pharyngeal arch that is posterior to the hyoid arch. i.e. any pharyngeal arch with a number 3 or higher.
An external projection of an aquatic animal as a fish used in propelling or guiding the body[BTO].
Volcano-shaped lateral line sensory organ located in characteristic positions within the skin epithelium and containing hair cells and their support elements.
Area of the parietal lobe concerned with receiving general sensations. It lies posterior to the central sulcus.
A parenchyma that is part of a lung.
The lobe of the left lung that is closest to the head.
A lower lobe of lung that is part of a left lung.
The distal portion of the colon; it develops embryonically from the hindgut and functions in the storage and elimination of waste.

Any exocrine gland whose cells bud their secretions off through the plasma membrane producing membrane-bound vesicles in the lumen; the apical portion of the secretory cell of the gland pinches off and enters the lumen; it loses part of its cytoplasm in their secretions; apocrine secretion is functional during hormonal stress or puberty; an example of true apocrine glands are mammary glands, responsible for secreting breast milk.
A dense regular connective tissue that that connects muscles together[WP, modified].
System pertaining to blood vessels in the brain.
An organism containing a developing embryo, fetus, or unborn offspring within the body.
A mature thymus that is entirely part of the cervical region.
A mature thymus that is entirely part of thoracic region.
Portion of tissue that projects outward from the gill and is a thread-like, soft, red respiratory and excretory structure.
The adenohypophyseal placode forms the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland and gives rise to the endocrine secretory cells of the pituitary.
The axilla is the area directly under the joint where the forelimb connects to the shoulder.
A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a midbrain.
A renal tubule is a tube that filters, re-absorbs and secretes substances to rid an organism of waste and to play a role in fluid homeostasis.
The part of the uterus above the isthmus and below the orifices of the uterine tubes.
Branch or outpocketing of the digestive tract.
Cranial ectodermal placode with potential to develop into a component of the nervous system, such as nerves or ganglia.
An epithelium that is part of a pancreatic duct.

Subcortical masses of gray matter in the forebrain and midbrain that are richly interconnected and so viewed as a functional system. The nuclei usually included are the caudate nucleus (caudoputamen in rodents), putamen, globus pallidus, substantia nigra (pars compacta and pars reticulata) and the subthalamic nucleus. Some also include the nucleus accumbens and ventral pallidum.
Any of the organized aggregations of cells that function as secretory or excretory organs and that release hormones in response to neural stimuli.
Any gland, other than the gonad, associated with the genital tract, such as the ampulla of the ductus deferens and the bulbourethral, prostate and vesicular glands of the male.
The core globe-shaped component of the camera-type eye.
Portion of tissue that is dorsolateral to the floor plate and part of the midbrain.
A single extraembryonic epithelium, which closes the germband dorsally.
A vasculature that is part of a conjunctiva.
The subserous connective tissue of the pelvic floor of the supracervical portion of the uterus. The parametrium extends laterally between the layers of the broad ligament.

definition.value: subserous coat of the uterus laterally between the layers of the broad ligament[MP] - todo - check relationships

value.value: Any layer of the epidermis that is superior to the stratum basale.

Paired fin skeleton that consists of the supporting endochondral proximal and distal radials and the dermal fins rays or lepidotrichia. The pectoral fin skeleton is located in the thoracic region of the body and articulates with the scapula and coracoid.
The collection of all meningeal layers that line a central nervous system.
A thin layer of cartilage, usually hyaline, on the articular surface of bones in synovial joints.
A cartilage element that is part of a splanchnocranium.
The dorsal portion of the first pharyngeal arch, comprising the upper jaw[ZFIN,VHOG].
Subdivision of urinary system which consists of the kidney and the ureters.
Any of the glands in silk-spinning insects and spiders that secrete a protein liquid that hardens into silk on exposure to air.
A gill that develops_from a pharyngeal gill precursor.
